se.cbb.jprime.topology

Class MPRMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.cbb.jprime.topology.MPRMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Dependent, ProperDependent

    public class MPRMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProperDependent
    Extends a guest-host map with functionality concerning the most parsimonious reconciliation when embedding the guest tree in the host tree using duplication and loss events. It is assumed that the guest-to-host leaf mapping does not change (nor the names), while the guest or host topologies may. See also LeafMap.

    Note: Only bifurcating trees supported at the moment.

    Author:
    Joel Sj√∂strand.

      • cacheAndUpdate

        public void cacheAndUpdate(java.util.Map<Dependent,ChangeInfo> changeInfos,
                  boolean willSample)
        Description copied from interface: ProperDependent
        Caches and updates this object. It may be assumed that this method will only be invoked if a parent has in fact changed.
        Input: All changes made so far, i.e., changes to dependent objects which precede this in the dependency DAG.
        Output: Changes made to this object are added to the input.

        Behaviour must adhere to the following:

        1. This objects queries input for change info of its parents.
        2. This object caches.
        3. This object sets its own change info (null if it has not changed).
        4. Exit.
        Specified by:
        cacheAndUpdate in interface ProperDependent
        Parameters:
        changeInfos - all changes made so far, including those of this objects parents, if any (null is interpreted as no change).
        willSample - true if the pending state will be sampled; false if not sampled. Invariant over any cacheAndUpdate()-clearCache()/restoreCache() cycle.

      • getSigma

        public int getSigma(int x)
        For x in V(G), returns the lowermost vertex/arc v in V(S) where x may be placed when reconciling G and S using only duplications and losses. More formally, sigma is a function f: V(G) -> V(S) where
        1. sigma(x) is the corresponding leaf in V(S) when x is a leaf.
        2. sigma(x) = LCA_{c in children(x)}(sigma(c)) otherwise.
        Parameters:
        x - the vertex of G.
        Returns:
        sigma(x).

      • isDuplication

        public boolean isDuplication(int x)
        Returns true if a vertex x of G is forced to be a duplication, i.e., it sigma(x)==sigma(y) or sigma(x)==sigma(z), where y and z are its children.
        Parameters:
        x - the vertex of G.
        Returns:
        true if x must be a duplication in the MPR; false otherwise.

      • getNoOfLossesOfArc

        public int getNoOfLossesOfArc(int x)
        For an edge e=(x,parent(x)) in the gene tree, returns the number of implied losses along e in a parsimonious reconciliation of the gene tree. If x is the root, the case is treated analogously.
        Parameters:
        x - the head vertex of the arc.
        Returns:
        the number of implied losses along the arc.
